/> <p> The servo Bit is a controllable motor that can swing back and forth! It has two modes: in “Turn” mode, the input from other littleBits determines the position of the arm – try using a dimmer to set the angle you want. In “Swing” mode, the servo will move back and forth on its own – the input controls how fast it goes. </p> </div> <div class="prez-slide"> <h3 class="pink"> Button </h3> <img /> <p> The button Bit push to turn your creation on, and release to turn it off. </p> <div class="prez-notes"> <p> The button module will make or break the signal path between two modules. When the button is pressed, the output of the module is directly connected to the signal line input. When not pressed the output of the module is weakly pulled low through a 1meg resistor. </p> </div> </div> <div class="prez-slide"> <h3 class="pink"> Dimmer </h3> <img
